‚ÄºÔ∏èAttention everyone in the ChatGPT Malaysia community‚ÄºÔ∏è
Recently, some vendors here in Malaysia have created "ChatGPT" named parallel apps to profit from those who are unaware and uneducated.
This is unfortunate and amounts to deception, but it is technically not illegal.
However, this can damage the trust of the original ChatGPT and cause people to misunderstand new technologies and AI.
We want to remind everyone that:
‚úÖ ChatGPT is 100% FREE to use with no limits (just not too many questoons per hr) for basic users.
‚úÖ You can use ChatGPT for free at http://chat.openai.com. There is no official app/WhatsApp/Telegram app for ChatGPT.
‚úÖ The only payment option is US$20 per month from the official ChatGPT platform for ChatGPT Plus.
‚õîÔ∏è Anyone else who asks you to buy "Tokens" or to pay even RM1 to download the "app" is not an official ChatGPT service.
Please help spread the word and share this information on all platforms to increase awareness.
Let's work together to ensure that everyone has access to the genuine ChatGPT and its benefits. Thank you üôèüèæ
Sources:
https://www.pcguide.com/apps/chat-gpt-free/
https://www.freemalaysiatoday.com/category/leisure/2023/02/07/watch-out-for-fake-chatgpt-apps/
-\-\-\-\-


‚ÄºÔ∏èPerhatian kepada semua anggota komuniti ChatGPT Malaysia! ‚ÄºÔ∏è
Baru-baru ini, beberapa penjual di Malaysia telah mencipta aplikasi selari yang dinamakan "ChatGPT" dalam cubaan untuk memperoleh keuntungan dari mereka yang tidak tahu dan tidak berpendidikan. Ini adalah suatu yang tidak diingini dan merupakan satu penipuan, tetapi secara teknikal ia tidak dilarang.
Walau bagaimanapun, ini boleh merosakkan keyakinan dan kepercayaan terhadap ChatGPT sebenar dan menyumbang kepada ketidakpercayaan terhadap teknologi baru dan AI.
Kami ingin mengingatkan semua bahawa:
‚úÖ ChatGPT adalah 100% PERCUMA digunakan tanpa had untuk pengguna asas, hanya terdapat had bilangan soalan yang boleh ditanya setiap jam
‚úÖ Anda boleh menggunakan ChatGPT secara percuma di http://chat.openai.com. Tidak ada aplikasi WhatsApp/Telegram rasmi untuk ChatGPT.
‚úÖ Satu-satunya pilihan pembayaran ialah US$20 sebulan dari platform ChatGPT rasmi untuk ChatGPT Plus.
‚õîÔ∏è Sesesiapa yang meminta anda untuk membeli "Token" atau membayar sekalipun RM1 untuk memuat turun "aplikasi" itu bukan perkhidmatan ChatGPT rasmi.
Sila bantu sebarkan maklumat ini di semua platform untuk meningkatkan kesedaran.
Mari bekerja bersama-sama untuk memastikan bahawa semua orang mempunyai akses kepada ChatGPT sebenar dan manfaatnya. Terima kasih üôèüèæ

text:
"Ke Mana, Penulisan?"
(English version below)
Cerita kita bersama penulisan bermula dalam bayangan samar gua-gua nenek moyang kita, di mana naratif diukir ke dalam batu dengan kayu yang primitif. Usaha pertama ini untuk merakam sejarah kita kasar, namun ia penuh makna dalam implikasinya.
Kemudian, kita menulis di atas daun-daun palma yang halus, sebagaimana yang dilakukan oleh orang India, menggunakan kelimpahan alam semulajadi untuk membawa cerita kita. Kemudian datanglah inovasi kertas oleh orang Cina, perkembangan yang mengubah landskap komunikasi secara dramatik, menawarkan kepada kita medium yang lebih serbaguna dan kekal.
Mesin percetakan tiba seterusnya, merevolusikan cara kita menyebarkan maklumat. Tiba-tiba, idea boleh berjalan jauh dan luas, tidak lagi terbatas kepada golongan elit tetapi tersedia untuk massa yang haus akan pengetahuan.
Mesin taip masuk ke dalam hidup kita seterusnya, kuncinya yang berirama memperkenalkan kecekapan dan keanggunan ke dalam seni menulis. Pejabat, bilik berita, dan meja penulis berdengung dengan irama idea yang dilahirkan dan dihantar keluar ke dunia.
Tidak dapat dielakkan, komputer muncul, menyatukan proses penulisan dengan alam semesta digital yang luas. Kekuatan pemprosesan kata mengubah tindakan menulis, menawarkan fleksibiliti dan kemudahan dalam cara-cara yang hanya kita mampu impikan sebelum ini.
Hari ini, kita berdiri di ambang transformasi lain, dengan AI generatif sebagai pemimpin. Penulisan menjadi seolah-olah tanpa usaha, seakan-akan angin sepoi-sepoi yang membawa fikiran kita terus ke skrin. Tetapi ke mana, kita mesti bertanya, angin ini membawa kita?
Kenaikan platform media sosial seperti Facebook dan Instagram telah menunjukkan kepada kita bahawa teknologi, sementara bertujuan untuk mendekatkan kita, seringkali dapat mencipta jurang yang tidak terlihat. Platform ini direka untuk menyambung kita, namun kita sering merasa lebih terpisah, hubungan kita menjadi lebih jauh.
Hal yang sama boleh dikatakan untuk AI generatif. Ia memudahkan proses penulisan, namun ia berisiko menjauhkan kita dari inti penulisan itu sendiri. Seperti kita meluncur di permukaan, adakah kita kehilangan sentuhan dengan kedalaman, perjuangan, keintiman, dan pertumbuhan peribadi yang dapat ditawarkan oleh penulisan?
Ke mana, penulisan? Ke mana arah perjalanan ini membawa kita? Seiring kita menerima perkembangan ini, kita harus waspada terhadap potensi kerugian. Teknologi adalah alat yang dapat membantu kita, tetapi ia tidak harus menenggelamkan sentuhan manusia unik yang memberi penulisan esensi dan makna sebenarnya. Saat kita melangkah maju, jangan kita lupa untuk membawa bersama kita hati, semangat, dan hubungan peribadi yang selalu menjadi inti dari penulisan.
-\-\
"Whither, Writing?"
Our story with writing began in the dim, flickering shadows of our ancestors' caves, where narratives were etched into stone with primitive sticks. These first attempts at recording our history were crude, yet they were profound in their implications.
From there, we found ourselves writing on the delicate leaves of palms, as the Indians did, making use of nature's abundance to carry our tales. Then came the Chinese innovation of paper, a development that shifted the landscape of communication dramatically, offering us a more versatile and enduring medium.
The printing press arrived next, revolutionizing the way we disseminated information. Suddenly, ideas could travel far and wide, no longer confined to the elite few but available to the hungry masses.
The typewriter clicked its way into our lives subsequently, its rhythmic keys introducing an efficiency and elegance to the art of writing. Offices, newsrooms, and writers' desks hummed with the music of ideas being born and sent out into the world.
Inevitably, the computer emerged, marrying the process of writing with the vast digital universe. The power of word processing transformed the act of writing, offering flexibility and simplicity in ways we could only dream of before.
Today, we stand on the brink of another transformation, with generative AI at the helm. Writing has become seemingly effortless, a breeze that carries our thoughts directly onto the screen. But where, we must wonder, is this breeze taking us?
The rise of social media platforms like Facebook and Instagram has shown us that technology, while intending to bring us closer, can often create unseen chasms. These platforms were designed to connect us, yet we find ourselves paradoxically distanced, our relationships diluted.
The same could be said for generative AI. It eases the process of writing, yet it risks alienating us from the very heart of it. As we glide on the surface, are we losing touch with the depths, the struggle, the intimacy, and the personal growth that writing can offer?
Whither, writing? Where does this path lead us? As we embrace these advancements, we must be wary of the potential loss. Technology is a tool that can aid us, but it must never overshadow the unique human touch that gives writing its true essence and meaning. As we move forward, let us not forget to bring with us the heart, the passion, and the personal connection that have always been at the core of writing.

Why Plugins?
‚úÖ With the plugins, ChatGPT becomes an interface with access to language models with tools.
‚úÖ These gives ChatGPT many new capabilities, such as extracting and explaining content directly from web pages, writing better code, or analysing and visualising data.
‚úÖ With plugins, ChatGPT can be connected with the internet (Finally!)
What are some interesting Plugins? ‚ùì
Code Interpreter: Acts like a junior programmer, helping you with coding tasks.
Visualiser: Transforms data into insightful visuals.
Web Browser: Lets ChatGPT access real-time information from the internet.
ChatwithPDF: Allows ChatGPT to access a PDF document and chat with the contents.
There are a total of 70 plugins available to use
How to access Plugins üñ•Ô∏è?
üñ•Ô∏è Right now, only ChatGPT Plus users can use plugins.
üñ•Ô∏è To turn them on, go to "Beta Features" in your settings.
-\-\
(Official Write-up by OpenAI: https://help.openai.com/en/articles/6825453-chatgpt-release-notes)

text:
Hello, nice to meet you all!üíú
My name is Bo-kyung Koo, and I am studying for a master's degree at the University of Malaya. As a computer engineeringüíª graduate, I have lots of interestes on AI, especially chat GPT. So I decided to start my master's research topic on continuous intentions to use chat GPT.
I'm sorry to interrupt your time, but your support and cooperation will be very helpful for my researchüåª. And I hope I can contribute to the development of the chatGPT industry. I would appreciate it if you could participate in the survey.
Participants in the survey can receive a small giftüéÅ. If you send me a capture of the survey through a Facebook message, I will send you an e-voucher of Startbucksü•Ø‚òï 10 of them randomly for expression of gratitude.
I look forward to your kind cooperation. And I hope many chatGPT users can participate in this surveyü•∞
Thank you so much.

DOCS.GOOGLE.COM
Determinants of continuance intention to use ChatGPT

g children to take up Multimedia, 3D artistry etc as opposed to real deep core software engineering and computer hardware architecture instead, with some two-point results: there was a bubble burst in the graphical artistry side of Computing, plus we had to import Programmers from India whenever we had wanted to do our own mundane Software needs.

text:
Web Browsing With ChatGPT

So I‚Äôll be delivering a talk to Top Glove Corporation about the uses of ChatGPT in an enterprise context in a few days and thought to look for a dataset so that I could illustrate some ChatGPT functionalities (data analysis, summaries, decision-making), and I thought to play around with ChatGPT‚Äôs new Web Browsing feature.

Here‚Äôs what ChatGPT did - it navigated multiple pages for me, did an evaluation process, performed searches, and eventually provided me with a perfectly formed dataset.

Incredible how AI is advancing in our world and truly fascinating to witness its progress!
